where: S, the slope, is a predetermined percentage of the detector signal, such as 80% as preferred in the illustration;


SC, the span calibration value, is the power required to energize the emitter to produce the predetermined detector signal;


CV, the zero calibration value, is the detector signal resulting from full power applied to the emitter;


DS, the raw detector signal, is produced upon applanating contact of the prism with a cornea; and


MV is the measured applanation value.
